   1:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c **** /**
   2:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * @file    system_stm32f1xx.c
   4:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * @author  MCD Application Team
   5:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * @brief   CMSIS Cortex-M3 Device Peripheral Access Layer System Source File.
   6:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * 
   7:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * 1.  This file provides two functions and one global variable to be called from 
   8:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *     user application:
   9:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *      - SystemInit(): Setups the system clock (System clock source, PLL Multiplier
  10:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                      factors, AHB/APBx prescalers and Flash settings). 
  11:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                      This function is called at startup just after reset and 
  12:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                      before branch to main program. This call is made inside
  13:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                      the "startup_stm32f1xx_xx.s" file.
  14:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *
  15:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClock variable: Contains the core clock (HCLK), it can be used
  16:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                                  by the user application to setup the SysTick 
  17:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                                  timer or configure other parameters.
  18:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                                     
  19:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *      - SystemCoreClockUpdate(): Updates the variable SystemCoreClock and must
  20:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                                 be called whenever the core clock is changed
  21:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *                                 during program execution.
  22:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *
  23:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * 2. After each device reset the HSI (8 MHz) is used as system clock source.
  24:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    Then SystemInit() function is called, in "startup_stm32f1xx_xx.s" file, to
  25:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    configure the system clock before to branch to main program.
  26:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *
  27:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   * 4. The default value of HSE crystal is set to 8 MHz (or 25 MHz, depending on
  28:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    the product used), refer to "HSE_VALUE". 
  29:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    When HSE is used as system clock source, directly or through PLL, and you
  30:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    are using different crystal you have to adapt the HSE value to your own
  31:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *    configuration.
  32:./f103/system_stm32f1xx.c ****   *        
